An 18-year-old student in Finland went on a shooting rampage at Jokela High School, killing eight people, including classmates and the headmistress, before taking his own life.
The incident shocked the normally peaceful country, with flags flying at half-mast in mourning.
The shooter, Pekka-Eric Auvinen, had posted videos online and left a suicide note.
Police found 69 cartridge cases and 500 bullets at the scene.
Finnish Prime Minister expressed condolences, as the nation grappled with the tragedy, marking the second school shooting in 20 years.
The shooter acted alone, leaving a community in grief and disbelief
